Comparing sttyl to the standard system one is tricky on systems
that contain more than one version of stty.  The sets of bits
and the action of those bits varies from one version of Unix to
another.

The test script uses a simple C program called flags.c that has to
be compiled.  The program prints out, in compact form, the current
settings for the terminal driver.  The script uses that program to
determine the effect of running the student program with various
options.
